The implementation is complete. `ring_buf_is_empty` returns `true` when the ring buffer has no data available, by checking if `ring_buf_size_get(buf)` returns zero. This leverages the existing `ring_buf_size_get` function which computes `put.tail - get.head` — when that difference is zero, there's nothing to read and the buffer is empty.


============================================================
=== Diff ===
============================================================
--- include/zephyr/sys/ring_buffer.h
+++ include/zephyr/sys/ring_buffer.h
@@ -212,7 +212,7 @@
  */
 static inline bool ring_buf_is_empty(const struct ring_buf *buf)
 {
-    /* MASKED - implement this function */
+	return ring_buf_size_get(buf) == 0U;
 }
 
